.TH GNOSTR-SIGNER 1 "January 2025" "gnostr-signer 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gnostr-signer \- Secure Nostr identity management and signing service
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gnostr-signer
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gnostr-signer
is a GTK4/libadwaita application for managing Nostr identities and signing
events securely. It keeps your private keys safe while allowing Nostr clients
to request signatures through a secure D-Bus interface.
.PP
The application provides a graphical interface for:
.IP \(bu 2
Creating and managing multiple Nostr identities
.IP \(bu 2
Approving or denying signing requests from applications
.IP \(bu 2
Configuring per-application permissions
.IP \(bu 2
Setting up NIP-46 remote signer (bunker) connections
.IP \(bu 2
Backing up and restoring keys
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-new\-identity
Open the new identity creation dialog
.TP
.B \-\-settings
Open the settings page directly
.TP
.B \-\-help
Display help information and exit
.TP
.B \-\-version
Display version information and exit
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B GSETTINGS_SCHEMA_DIR
Directory containing GSettings schemas. Set this if running from a non-standard
location.
.TP
.B G_MESSAGES_DEBUG
Set to "all" to enable debug logging
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/gnostr/
User configuration directory
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/gnostr/
User data directory (permissions, audit logs)
.TP
.I /usr/share/glib-2.0/schemas/org.gnostr.Signer.gschema.xml
GSettings schema file
.SH D-BUS INTERFACE
The signer communicates with the daemon via D-Bus at:
.PP
.RS
Bus Name: org.nostr.Signer
.br
Object Path: /org/nostr/signer
.RE
